DATASET
-------
The plant dataset shipped under /data (data/plants.json) is licensed under
Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International
(CC BY-NC-SA 4.0):  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Why CC BY-NC-SA, finalized in Workplan Stage 1.5 (see
docs/adr/0009-dataset-merge-and-licensing.md for the full reasoning):

  The sources actually shipped in the current artifact do NOT by themselves
  compel NonCommercial — the content is OpenFarm (CC0-1.0, a public-domain
  dedication) plus original curation (hand-verified spacing figures, which are
  facts and not themselves copyrightable; and the companion/antagonist links).
  Plants For A Future (PFAF) — the CC BY-NC-SA source whose share-alike terms
  drive this choice — is NOT yet ingested: its download endpoint is blocked by
  the build sandbox's egress policy (the same class of block that keeps GBIF
  unreachable; see docs/adr/0006). So today's content alone could ship under a
  more permissive licence.

  The dataset is nonetheless held at CC BY-NC-SA deliberately: it is the
  project's ratified stance (WORKPLAN.md §0.5), the project is non-commercial by
  design, and PFAF is the intended primary source of growing-requirement data
  (DESIGN.md §2). Holding the eventual target from the start avoids relicensing
  already-released data the moment PFAF lands. CC BY-NC-SA is a valid, more
  restrictive licence for a compilation of CC0 content, so there is no conflict.

